rComments: Shelly is hilarious and carefree. His exams aren't hard but you do have to read the textbook. I found his exam questions about lecture material confusing at times due to wording, but I did fine on the exams. He retired this year. :( All the best to you Shelly!

Sheldon Ungar is an amazing prof who makes coming to class actually fun. He swears a lot but is pretty funny.  We just had a midterm and a final for the course but it wasn't too bad. You literally read the textbook and take notes in class and you'll be fine for the exam. He also sometimes goes over questions in class before the exam that help.

Long lectures but they rarely go the full 3 hours. Ungar is pretty good and always making jokes but he can come off as a bit arrogant. His lectures are either really interesting or really boring, but regardless attendance is mandatory. He doesn't post the slides with info online. The exams aren't too hard but not that easy either.
Read the textbook religiously and you will do great!
The course itself is great, the prof did not do it justice.
Awesome prof. Keep up with readings and attend lectures and you'll do fine. Exam is 50/50 and if you study an A is achievable
Entertaining
Love his lectures! Exams are impossible but I somehow managed to do really well in his class :s
Don't skip class- half his exams were based on his lectures!

Hilarious, crude and does not care what anyone else thinks of him. Clear that he knows what he's talking about in lectures. Bases his exams off both lectures and textbook readings pretty evenly. I found it kind of hard to ask questions since there are so many students in the class, but he does give great answers when you talk to him individually.

rComments: He's an amazing prof overall. Easily approached and absolutely hilarious.  Read your textbook and go to class and you'll do well. He's easy to come to and ask questions because he's so friendly. Exams are 50% in class stuff and 50% textbook and are very easy to pass. Highly recommend any class with him. 201415

rComments: Pretty funny, if you don't think he's at least kind of funny you probably have no sense of humor. Lectures are really long. Gonna be brutally honest about this class: sometimes I forgot I was even in it. I never read anything. I hardly ever payed attention in class and didn't study for either exam and still finished with a 71.

The professor is very interesting to listen to, even though he goes off topic a lot. To do well in this class,  you need to go to lectures and take notes since the exams are 50% lecture +50% textbook.

Lectures can put you to sleep unless you sit up front. Exams are brutal if you don't study. If it's required for your program, attendance & readings are a must. If it's an elective, you either take it seriously or you don't and miss every lecture. Have that CRNCR ready.

rComments: Great Prof.
He is very disorganized and ineffective in lectures.  He rants and tells little side jokes that (only) he laughs at.  His exams are half textbook and half lecture, therefore attendance is mandatory.

Took this course because my friend said it was easy, so I thought it'd boost my GPA. It actually lowered my GPA.                                   But overall, the course is pretty easy. But if you want a 4.0, DO NOT study last minute. Maybe study 2 days or 3 days before the midterm. Got a 71 on a midterm because EVERYTHING in the book is fair game

His exams are usually textbook based but the final exam in SOCA02 was brutal. His exams are usually out of 100 and almost half the exam is questions he makes up from lectures, and they are so detail-specific. He's funny but SOOO hard!!

Funny prof, keeps lectures interesting. Fairly hard midterm/final. The textbook questions on the exams were fairly easy. The lecture questions from the exams were killer. Must take pay attention and take notes to do well in this course.

I looked forward to attending his lectures every week, his mannerisms reminded me of myself.  Really intelligent, witty and sarcastic and used many fantastic examples.  I will look for further courses that he teaches.

social stats..guy mumbles ALOT, thinks everyone should know the complicated material, makes zero sense and tells you its a waste of his time to help, his exams aren't too bad and the TA was heaven-sent! lectures were optional but tutorials helped since she did his job for him. basically had to teach ourselves the material through the textbook.
Was an amazing soc teacher. I learned a lot in his class, and he was hilarious to say the least.... Also easy on the eyes.

He is a funny and interesting prof. He is great at explaining concepts, and uses a lot of examples. His exams are fair. Short answers mainly from lec, and M/C from text. Need to go to classes and take notes. Wish I had him for the 2nd part of intro soc! I hear he is actually difficult in upper level courses though...
Irresistibly witty & sarcastic. I've decided to take any other course Ungar does.
delicious and yet very nutritious.
fun prof!!!
This guy is awesome. His jokes are funny. The best thing is his exams structure. Its basically his lecture notes and textbook mcq's. Really easy.

AWESOME prof. had him for A01 as well. He's very vulgar and offensive at times, but he knows his stuff and can keep your attention for 3 hours. that's saying alot considering the material can be boring at times.
He was NOT boring. Out of all my classes this one always the hardest to find a seat in. I found the class easy and interesting. Take the course!
